Iranian students are ready to die for their country’s core program.
They were a living shield.
A few hundred college students formed a living shield around a nuclear object in Iran.
With this gesture, they wanted to demonstrate their support for their country’s nuclear program before a possible Israeli attack.
The students had prayed in front of the object on Tuesday afternoon and then announced death to the United States and Israel.
A few hundred students from the university in Isfahan, Iran, formed a live sign around the nuclear technology center in Isfahan, where uranium is processed.
