But so that we can not only listen, but also try something practical, we learned how to properly glue shoes.
Even when photographing in the studio, where the floor is flat, you can damage the shoe sole, let alone the outside.
We were sticking and we were sticking...
The scissors should not even touch the shoes, so as not to damage them.
So you really have to be smart.
Mario delighted me by praising my "creation" without restrictions.
The skill mentioned above is not exactly my strength.
All this was only a fraction of what we heard during the second weekend of the continuation course.
One thing has now become clear to me - dedicating yourself to styling on a professional level is not a child's play.
V Need for Speed: "The Run" - the illegal race across America
Review:
The original carefree ride is made possible by a series of completely avoidable, dilettante errors for the routine ride to the early stage.
Although it was possible to fulfill the ambitions for the most part, but what good is this, if obviously no one wanted to do a little more.
Even before he came to the store tables, the new part with the subtitle "The Run" aroused high expectations.
He promised to move the already aged game series "Need for Speed" to a new dimension again and in the playable demonstration examples he did not seem to be just one of many action racing games.
We were also curious how the fit passages turn out, in which the main protagonist gets out of the car and continues on foot.
But as you are accustomed to with NFS, in the end it is much different than expected.
Sure - potentially it's quite decent arcade racing, but overall, the game is diminished by some superfluous mistakes that have been present in this series for more or less a few years.
So they are no longer mistakes, but rather signs of a fundamentally incomprehensible laziness of game developers.
The adventure starts very well.
For the first time, you are introduced to the story, whose main character Jack has certain problems of personal character; the only solution seems to be to participate in an illegal race across America.
In San Francisco, that is, on the west coast, you sit at the wheel - with the task of being the first in New York.
The basic idea includes a whole range of interesting elements.
The entire route is divided into ten stages and more than fifty individual races.
This means that each race is held on a different track and that the individual stages take place in a different, sufficiently different and interesting environment.
It doesn’t seem like the game will offer the same thing over and over again.
Some environments are still very nice to look at, although the technical level of the graphics does not go beyond that of the previous parts of the series.
So nothing world-moving.
But the drive through the desert, through the autumnal landscape or high up through the deep snowy landscape seems visually very pleasant.
From time to time, atypical elements bring a little variation into the individual races.
In the desert, for example, you are surprised by a desert storm that severely restricts your vision.
In the mountains, you have to be careful not to be spilled by an avalanche.
By the way, the individual races are quite well built up.
Only a few, but they are enough.
For a while you try to overcome the required number of opponents (in principle a classic race), then you have time to catch up (classic race against the stopwatch), then you expect another personal duel with a single opponent.
And then there's the police, who want to mess you up.
A novelty are passages in which Jack leaves the car.
It’s more about some interactive animations in which Jack runs away from someone and where the player has to help him by pressing the right button at the right moment.
So, nothing complicated.
However, it is surprising that there are far fewer such passages in the game than you would expect (in particular, only three).
Ultimately, this is more to the advantage, because at least this element does not have a chance to get bored - it is one of the elements that make the game more varied in the context of the above.
The driving model follows in the footsteps of the previous parts.
That is, from today's point of view, it does not pluck any trees, on the other hand, one could not claim that it would be bad.
If you are looking for realistic simulations, you need to look elsewhere.
But for an action-packed race, the local driving model will still be quite fair, although you could find better in the competition.
Until then, everything is in good order.
Real problems only arise after a certain amount of time.
Unlike the driving model, the collision model is not entirely OK.
A game of this kind is hardly expected to calculate complicated deformations and collisions, but if you have virtually no idea of how the car behaves before an impact on any object, then obviously everything is not okay.
Typical example: When passing by or passing by on opposite cars, you "strip" the other car only slightly in some places, but in other, almost identical situations you get into the swing and turn wild pirouettes.
Or the car just goes to waste.
Thanks to the restart system, it doesn’t matter anymore, it’s always annoying.
The restarts are solved in this way: if you have total damage or land far away from the track, then the game throws you back to the last point of the track.
Only - in each race you have only five restarts.
Once you’ve exhausted it, everything starts from the beginning.
So the restarts are more like a tool, in case something fails, but you shouldn’t rely on it.
Sometimes, however, even the restart doesn’t help, as nothing else helps but learning the critical section out of your head.
It’s very unpleasant that the same things often happen in the same places.
For example, some curves have to be passed in a very specific way, otherwise you simply do not pass through.
In other places, you will always find "civil" cars in the same configuration, whether you come first or fifth, five seconds earlier or a minute later.
This is especially annoying in situations when you see the opponent passing in front of a playing two opposing cars, but by the time you get there yourself, the cars are already in such a position that you have to bypass or brake them.
And no matter when you get there, everything is designed in such a way that this situation always comes close to your nose.
The contractors have other advantages.
Throughout the game there are a few places where you are always overtaken at the same place by the same opponent and here again regardless of the time.
The most crazy thing is to finish the game on the long bridge, which you pass in the opposite direction.
The contractor obviously has to get one out here on the devil's ass.
And if he is in front of you, then of course he takes your sights, so that at first you drive your own car a few times in Klump.
Of course - you just want to make the game more exciting and exciting, but this intention is so clear that it will quickly lose you the joy of the game.
And that’s a shame, because despite the simpler driving model, the game as a whole is quite entertaining and sometimes so action-packed that you almost don’t know where one’s head is.
And in principle, it doesn't matter what the "guilty" is - the concept of fifty unique routes, the arrangement of the races in such a way that no boredom can arise, or something completely different...
An unusual idea is also the change of car during the races.
You should not overlook the gas stations on the route, because right here you can change the car, although in most cases the car you just have is enough.
The cars are divided into three categories.
The sports cars are well suited for urban areas, the strong American limousines for the straight highways and exotic super sports cars for the technical rides, for example on the serpentines in the mountains.
Hand in hand with the game history mode also goes the task mode (challenges) - that is, the races in the individual locations that you know from the story.
Here there are not only medals, but also experience points for your own profile, which is common for the tasks (challenges) and history.
To get to the higher driver level, various items must be unlocked: from the car to the backgrounds for the profile.
At the same time, this is connected to the online function Autolog, which, among other things, compares its own achieved results with those of other players and also provides for further collective functions.
One of the other incomprehensible carvers is a situation in the last race of history.
Here you can get by car into a subway tunnel (my way), where you can ride long on the rails in the dark (my way).
On the tacho, figures look between 150 and 200 km/h (for me), but suddenly from the back comes a subway and drives an uncompromising dirt.
In our editorial office, we will probably argue for a long time about whether this was a blackout of the game designers or whether the authors think we are so stupid.
The technical side is nothing overwhelming but at least the overall visual impression is quite appealing in most cases and even brilliant here and there.
It is all the more annoying that in some exciting moments the frame rate becomes slower and this is sometimes quite dramatic.
This, however, particularly applies to accidents with a larger number of participants, where a continuous FPS is of no use to you anyway.
The sound playback is OK and the soundtrack is a matter of taste.
In an effort to reach as large a scale as possible rather young audiences, a soundtrack a lá "of everyone something" was created - but who buys such a game because of the music?!
The overall impression of Need for Speed: The Run? The feelings are rather mixed.
If the game weren’t diminished by the aforementioned totally unnecessary errors, we could have argued with the chest tone of belief that The Run is the best piece of NFS in recent years.
This is how the game seems to be unfinished.
It’s a great pleasure in itself, but you should be prepared to face these mistakes with the power of airport headlights.
