She would also have liked to use the EU’s soil to get more Czechs into European institutions.
A Europe of two or different speeds in perspective
According to the EU ambassador, the Czechs are called to be Eurosceptics, who perceive more the negative than the positive sides of the matter.
The weak representation of Czechs in European institutions is all the more annoying.
This is due to many factors, including the restraint of our candidates, their inability to write letters of motivation and, last but not least, the weak support of the Czech side.
In addition to the successful Czech presidency, she also highlighted the strength and cooperation of the Visegrad Group, the so-called V4.
"Believe me, if a Pole or Hungarian comes to me and a Slovak is nearby, then the Frenchman next to me thinks, 'Hey, what are you putting your heads together - is this your V4 again?'
According to Vicenové, the EU expects in the future, above all, tough rules on the budgetary policies of the member states.
As much more real than a "European federation", she sees the concept of a Europe of two or even different speeds.
