This allowed us to transform technology, business and society in the course of our first century.
We hope to achieve even more in the next hundred years,” said Samuel J. Palmisano, the company’s current director on the occasion of the anniversary.
A well-thought-out system
Watson was already socially caring for his employees in the 1930s - in a similar way to the entrepreneur Ba<0xC4><0x8D>a in Czechoslovakia: IBM people had paid vacation as one of the first American employees, insurance by the entrepreneur plus elegant uniforms as workwear and a thoughtful pay-back system for best new employees.
