“From the beginning, IBM had the concept of an institution rather than a mere technology company,” said the Harvard Business School professor and author of a book on IBM, Rosabeth Moss Kanter.
“IBM is not a technology company, but a company that helps solve business problems using technology,” added George Colony of consulting firm Forrester Research.
As the company itself emphasizes, it makes a difference to be only present on the market or to shape it directly through this presence.
