Black labor
The analysis of the labour market in Sinaloa is even more serious, taking into account the high share of black labour, which, according to INEGI, includes 60.38 percent of the country’s employees who work without paying into the social security funds.
Unemployment and black labor are the lowest wages in all of Mexico, according to statistics from the Instituto Mexicano del Seguro Social and the Secretaria del Trabajo y Previsión Social.
