The debts
In the face of the economic crisis, the state government applied for a loan of 3 000 000 000 pesos at the National Congress in July to be invested in infrastructure projects in the 18 municipalities in order to reactivate the economy.
Reactions
For the representatives of entrepreneurship, Mario López Valdés’ first year of government made government incapacity obvious.
Miguel Loredo López, chairman of the Cámara Nacional de la Industria de la Transformación (Mexico’s national chamber of manufacturing), said that in 2011 no efforts were made to harmonize the views of the different sectors, including the state government.
