The court approves for 2015 the transition to digital television in Mexico
The transition from analog to digital signals has been one of the most important changes in the world in recent years.
The Supreme Court of Mexico (SCJN) dismissed the constitutional lawsuits filed by the Senate and House of Representatives against the presidential decree, and under which the switch from analogue to digital signals must be postponed from 2021 to 2015, due to the lack of eight votes required to challenge the law.
