We make sure not to be on tour too often because it’s too easy to fall for this game with huge crowds who love your music.
As long as you remember that people came because of the music, it reminds you that you have to pay attention to the music and what it brought into life, without failing to be a famous rock star.
What memories do you have of your other Mother Love Bone project?
I think we wrote very good songs and at the beginning it was great.
For three years, we were a band that had never released a record until the death of Andy (Andrew Woods).
We were disappointed to have spent so long together. We are still good friends with Bruce (Fairweather) and Greg (Gilmore), who built the band with us. When I hear a song or see photos, I think about what an incredible man Andy was walking and how he made me laugh. It was always fun to talk to others and la freude
