There are so many that I could talk all afternoon about the bassist I like.
How did Pearl Jam manage to keep Grunge alive even though it’s no longer a fashion phenomenon?
I think we all don’t feel very connected to the word grunge.
When I think about it, I think about the bands I mentioned before, like Mudhoney, Soundgarden, Nirvana and all the others that came up at the same time. If they are still important today, I think it's great because it's worth listening to this music and bands like Mudhoney are making better music now than ever before.
At first her music was darker, now she is more positive.
What's that?
