Colom guarantees the delivery of portillos to the United States
Guatemalan President <0xC3><0x81>lvaro Colom announced on Tuesday that he would host the extradition of former governor Alfonso Portillo to hold him accountable in the United States for the $70 million money laundering conspiracy.
Thus, the process ends with the U.S. request for Portillo’s extradition so that he can be brought to court there.
